  "prompt": "What type of antenna is used in mobile phone receivers?",
  "response": "In mobile phones, several types of antennas are used depending on the specific design and technology. The most common types include:\n\n1. Patch Antenna\n- Compact and planar design\n- Used for cellular and wireless communications\n- Provides good performance in a small form factor\n\n2. Microstrip Antenna\n- Printed directly on the circuit board\n- Lightweight and low-profile\n- Suitable for mobile devices with space constraints\n\n3. Monopole Antenna\n- Simple vertical antenna\n- Typically used for basic cellular communications\n- Often integrated within the phone's body\n\n4. MIMO (Multiple Input Multiple Output) Antenna\n- Uses multiple antenna elements\n- Improves signal reception and data transmission\n- Supports modern cellular technologies like 4G and 5G\n\n5. Diversity Antenna\n- Uses two or more antennas to improve signal reception\n- Helps reduce signal fading and improve overall performance\n\n6. Ceramic Antenna\n- Small, compact design\n- Good for high-frequency communications\n- Used in modern smartphones\n\nThe specific antenna type can vary based on the phone manufacturer, model, and intended communication technology.",
